verbose_text: The outcomes revealed that the intervention of GSK-3beta inhibitors alleviated the pathological damage of pancreas and lung (P < 0.01), reduced serum amylase, lipase, hydrothorax and lung Wet-to-Dry Ratio, attenuated serum concentrations of IL-1beta and IL-6 (P < 0.01), inhibited the activation of NF-kappaB, and abated expression of iNOS, ICAM-1 and TNF-alpha protein, but up-regulated IL-10 expression in lung of ANP rats (P < 0.01).
